brief: The function RetriggerSI_DiagnoseAktivTimer just sets the timer variable "SI_DiagnoseAktivTimer" to "SI_DIAGNOSEAKTIV_TIMER_START_VALUE" (400 > 4 s).
detailed: It shall be called in order to retrigger the timer when diagnostic messages (CAN/100BaseTx) are received and thus a diagnostic is active. (see EA)

brief: The function DiagnosticTimersSetDefaultSessionState is called when the diagnosis session changes, for example due to request of Service "Diagnostic Session Control" (SID 10hex) by the diagnosis tester (client).
detailed: It stores the information, if the the new diagnosis session is the DefaultSession or not, in a static variable for further use by other internal functions. This information is given via the boolean function parameter "state" by the caller of this function.

brief: The function RetriggerTDiagEnableTimer just sets the timer variable "T_Diag_Enable" to "DIAG_ENABLE_TIMER_START_VALUE_ON_KL15OFF" (9000 > 900 s = 15 minutes).
detailed: It shall be called if transition from KL15_ON to KL15_OFF is detected.

brief: The function RetriggerNMDiagActiveTimer sets the timer T_NM_DiagActive to either 40 s or 4 s - depending on the variable "Trasition35Requested" - if the preconditions for retriggering the timer T_NM_DiagActive (as stored in the variable "DiagEnableStatus") are fulfilled.
detailed: It is shall be called if

brief: The function DiagnosticTimersNotifyDiagnoseActiveStatus is called due to the so called "Transition 35".
detailed: "Transition 35" = Change from NonDefaultSession to DefaultSession due to KL15_OFF to KL15_ON (see SWR_ICAS_Diag_99). In the function parameter "TransitionProcessed" the transition status is given.

brief: The function DiagnosticTimersNotifyDiagnoseActiveStatus is called if the diagnosis activation status changes (becomes active and incative) and the new activation status is passed as argument in the function parameter "NewStatus".
detailed: It checks the precondition "Default diagnosis session is active", and if it's true, it calls the function "RetriggerNMDiagActiveTimerOnDiagnosticRequest" in order to to update the timer "NM_DiagActive" and the status "DiagnosticActive" (as long as further conditions are fulfilled)

brief: The function DiagnosticTimersCyclic shall be called cyclically every 10ms.
detailed: It processes the timers "T_NM_DiagActive" and "T_Diag_Enable" as well as the related status informations every 100 ms (using a prescaler).

brief: The function getStateKL15TimerForDrivingCycle just returns the status of the "KL15 timer for driving cycle".

desc.param_desc: TimerState - Status of the "KL15 timer for driving cycle" which is counted every 10 ms

brief:
The function getConditionVehicleSpeed just returns the validation status of vehicle speed processing which is verified cyclically (every 100 ms) 
 Background: Some diagnosis services require preconditions to be fulfilled, in order to allow their execution.
detailed: One of the preconditions is that the velocity (vehicle speed) is within a certain range. This function returns the result of this velocity precondition check.

desc.param_desc: ConditionVehicleSpeed - Result of the velocity precondition check done cyclically every 100 ms

brief: Implementation of diagnostic timers - NM_DiagActive, T_DiagEnable, KL15 timer for Driving Cycle validation.
4000ms/10ms UdsTask cycle

enum_vars.name: TIMER_ELAPSED
enum_vars.desc: 0 - Timer elapsed in the last cyclic processing

enum_vars.name: TIMER_RUNNING
enum_vars.desc: 1 - Timer is running and decremented cyclically

enum_vars.name: TIMER_RESTARTED
enum_vars.desc: 3 - Timer was set to start value in the last cyclic processing

enum_vars.name: PASSED
enum_vars.desc: 0 - Velocity preconditions for execution of diagnosis services are fulfilled

enum_vars.name: FAILED
enum_vars.desc: 1 - Velocity preconditions for execution of diagnosis services are NOT fulfilled
